                     <handNote xml:id="h2" script="Ethiopic">quire I (Text I-1). The script is characterized by small letters with short hairlines. Many letters have forked hook vowel markers (e.g., ብ, ን, ገ).</handNote>
                     <handNote xml:id="h3" script="Ethiopic">quires II-XIV (Texts I-2 until I-13). The handwriting is regular throughout the Ms. (except at the very end, s. fol. 101r) with rounded, upright letters.</handNote>
